==English==
===Adjective===
'''fungible'''
# (''law'') [[goods]] which are consumed when they are used, such as food or ink
# (''of a debt'') able to be [[substituted]] for something of [[equal]] [[value]]
# [[interchangeable]]

===Etymology===
This word comes through the Latin word "'''fungere'''", meaning 'to perish' or 'to consume'.

